tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt: 52nd qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.curYearHigh: Finished fourth at PGA TOUR Canada Qualifying School outside Orlando to earn exempt status for 2014...In first 10 starts, managed two top-25 finishes, including a solo 12th at the Bayview Place Island Savings Open. In 11th start of the season, opened with three rounds in the 60s to hold a share of the 54-hole lead with Michael Gligic at the Cape Breton Celtic Classic. Posted final-round 73 to finish two shots out of the Mark Silvers-Matt Harmon playoff won by Silvers...Shot a bogey-free final round 64 at the TOUR Championship of Canada to post the clubhouse lead at 12-under and finish two shots back of eventual winner Ryan Williams... Top-four finishes in each of his final two weeks were enough to put him 20th on the Order of Merit, securing him an exemption into the second stage of Web.com Tour Qualifying School.
tourBios.carHigh: Played on the Canadian Tour and Hooters Tour from 2007-12. 2010: Qualified for the U.S. Open at Pebble Beach GL but missed the cut. 2012: Advanced to the final stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament for the first time and earned conditional status on the Web.com Tour after finishing T139. 2009: Made his professional debut on the Web.com Tour, at the Northeast Pennsylvania Classic, finishing 68th
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was named to the all-state golf team in 2003 at Christian Brothers Academy in Syracuse, N.Y...Was an honorable mention All-American in 2005 and 2007...Made his Web.com Tour debut as an amateur at the 2006 Northeast Pennyslvania Classic (missed cut).
tourBios.personal: Biggest thrill in golf was playing in the 2010 U.S. Open...Would round out his dream foursome with Tom Watson, Ken Venturi and Ben Hogan...Favorite movie is "Forrest Gump."
